Program: Discovery
Title: Beeches Pit
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx61
Last Broadcast Date: 11 August 1998
A discussion with Dr. John Gowlett and archaeologists working at Beeches Pit in England. Around 400,000 years ago an intelligent tool-making species lives in Suffolk, East Anglia, UK. These hominids, who were not ancestors of modern man, could tell us about our own evolution. Presenter: Pauline Newman. Show less